node.text: @jonnyboyeats These satays are succulent and tasty! 😋😋😋

DIY beef satay using marinated meats & made some ketupat/rice cake (recipe below) to go with the peanut sauce that comes with every purchase of 1kg frozen marinated satay meat from Lau Pa Sat Best Satay Stall 7 & 8. (Swipe to 👀 video on how these are being prepared).
.
.

My family enjoyed these beef satay very much! My girl was initially skeptical when I placed order for beef instead of chicken cos in her mind beef satay meat is usually quite tough. How wrong she was when she tasted it as the beef satays are succulent and tasty!!! 😋👍😍
.

Now, it is being offered on Klook app with delivery as well as exclusive promotion of $22 for a kilogram of marinated satay meat (available in Chicken, Beef, & Mutton) and comes with a packet of 500g satay peanut sauce.
.

Do check out Klook website for more promotions:
🌐 https://bit.ly/KlookRamadan.
🌐 https://bit.ly/KlookChefInBox.
.
. . 【𝐄𝐚𝐬𝐲 𝐊𝐞𝐭𝐮𝐩𝐚𝐭 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞- 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐫 
𝐌𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐨𝐝 𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐛𝐲 𝐁𝐚𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐢】
𝙄𝙣𝙜𝙧𝙚𝙙𝙞𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙨:
2 cups short grain rice
3.5 cups water
.

𝙈𝙚𝙩𝙝𝙤𝙙𝙨: (𝙨𝙬𝙞𝙥𝙚🔙☝️𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙥𝙝𝙤𝙩𝙤 𝙧𝙚𝙛𝙚𝙧𝙚𝙣𝙘𝙚)
1. Wash & drain rice. Place rice and water in the inner pot of rice cooker. Select "rice setting" to cook.

2. After cooking is done, immediately transfer rice to a loaf pan lined with food grade cling wrap. Press down with rice paddle as you transfer. After finished transferring, cover the top surface with another piece of cling wrap. Use hand to compress down and smooth the surface.

3. Poke the cling wrap with a skewer to create holes for steam to escape. Let cool a little and put into fridge for an hour before cutting into 1 inch cube.
.
.

Thank you Best Satay Stall 7&8 for sending the marinated meat and satay sauce over and KlookSG for arranging. .
.
.
.
